isExternal

public boolean isExternal()
True if this class is provided externally to the program by the program's host execution environment. For example, while compiling for the JVM, JRE types are external types. External types definitions are provided by class files which are considered opaque by the GWT compiler. TODO(scottb): Means something totally different after AST stiching is done.
